    {
      "Text": "Security update for libXfont",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for libXfont fixes several issues.\n\nThese security issues were fixed:\n\n- CVE-2017-13720: Improper check for end of string in PatterMatch caused invalid reads (bsc#1054285)\n- CVE-2017-13722: Malformed PCF file could have caused DoS or leak information (bsc#1049692)\n- Prevent the X server from accessing arbitrary files as root. It is not possible to leak information, but special files can be touched allowing for causing side effects (bsc#1050459)\n\nThis update was imported from the SUSE:SLE-12-SP2:Update update project.",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
